==={{initialism}}===
'''AD'''<BR>
'''A.D.'''

# Latin ''[[anno Domini]]'', [[in the year of our Lord]], used to specify numbered years counting from the once estimated birth of Christ in AD 1.
# Assistant Director.

====Usage notes====
* The [[w:Chicago Manual of Style|Chicago Manual of Style]] as well as most house styles require placing the '''A.D.''' before the date (e.g., AD 250), although in casual use it is frequently found following the date.
*Many authors prefer to use [[CE]] ([[Common Era]]), which avoids Christian bias.

